data.title: 26 fun facts for October, 27 (+3 bonus) - Historical events, discover what happened on this day.
data.meta_description: On October 27th, events like the inauguration of the New York City Subway, Theodore Roosevelt's birth, the launch of Apple's iPad Mini, and the establishment of the United Nations Emergency Force took place. On this date, famous personalities such as Joaquin Phoenix, John Oliver, and Kelly Osbourne were born, while the largest outbreak of Ebola was declared over in Nigeria.
